LongDescription: These ships were designed for moving free-floating materials and ships around maintenance yards.  They have excellent maneuverability and plenty of space to support a variety of different missions now that they've been pressed into military service.
FlavorText:
Constantine,

I've spoken with Abel Drake of Bulwark and he has given us his fleet of "Draugr" tugboats for use as an auxiliary warship. They're not much but they're hardy vessels and they should give us some flexibility in deploying some of our own EWAR. As I understand it, Vance has proposed using them as picket ships with Linebackers but I'll leave the tactical assessment to your capable hands.

These aren't designed for warfare, most of these date back to when Armas Sikke took up the Barony of Pyxis, but the Otdel made a concentrated effort to convert most of the civilian systems into military-capable vessels, so you shouldn't have too hard of a time to fit these to your needs. I wish we could have a couple of Sprinters on hand but the Alliance doesn't like to share, it seems.

- Amelie, Logistics Command
